Getting Started
To run this project on your local machine, follow these steps:

Clone this repository to your local machine.
Install the required dependencies by running npm install in the root directory of the project.
Create a MongoDB database and import the given JSON dataset into it.
Update the DB_CONNECTION variable in the .env file to point to your MongoDB database.
Start the server by running npm run server in the root directory of the project.
Start the client by running npm run client in a separate terminal window.
Features
The dashboard includes the following features:

A scatter plot that displays the intensity and likelihood of each event in the dataset.
A bar chart that displays the number of events by year.
A world map that displays the number of events by country.
Filters that allow users to filter events by end year, topics, sector, region, PEST, and source.
Interactive charts and graphs that update in real-time as the filters are applied.
Technologies Used
This project uses the following technologies:

MongoDB: A NoSQL database used to store the dataset.
Express.js: A web application framework for Node.js used to create the API.
React: A JavaScript library used to create the front-end of the dashboard.
Node.js: A JavaScript runtime used to run the server-side code.
D3.js: A JavaScript library used to create the visualizations.
Bootstrap: A front-end framework used to style the dashboard
